    },
    {
      "id": "FCZIQhOEl8vcui0RD2diK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2291.8468155749424,
      "y": 3491.138818605292,
      "width": 1246.259033203125,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0Y",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 14170873,
      "version": 373,
      "versionNonce": 1822995095,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "3OgaZK8KNEHsHa1f2CE0m",
          "type": "arrow"
        },
        {
          "id": "zn9-TGPc7cOWDsolr3k7M",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1777140211988,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Thus, By this method, Alice and Bob if they together work also -> Have Problem in resolving Conflict and see differernt word !!\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Thus, By this method, Alice and Bob if they together work also -> Have Problem in resolving Conflict and see differernt word !!\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PwYAr8nfSb0wTGLO4PrK3",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2099.873623676325,
      "y": 3589.3598749761454,
      "width": 1445.522705078125,
      "height": 1041.3545893777941,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0Z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1088634841,
      "version": 1743,
      "versionNonce": 1349935225,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777140211960,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4. Alogrithms to Resolve this merge conflict are:  [** This is the core of this collaborative user based Problems ** ]\n    \n1. OT  - Operational Transformation\n        -  Transforms Concurrent Operations during Merging.\n        - The transformation fnc ensures that the effect of operation is adjusted to account for the changes by other  operation.  \n\n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n   \n       \n    \n    Problems: \n            1. The Operations must go through a particular server that handles the Transformation.\n            2. Implementation is a bit complex.\n    \n\n!!! Google uses this OT way to solve the Merge Conflict Problem !!!\n\n\n\n2. CRDT - Conflict Free Repicated Data Types:\n    - CRDT is a data structures designed for the distribured system that automatically resolve conflicts caused by concureent updates.\n    - This ensures eventual consitiency without requirimg coordinate by using mathematical properties that allow operations to merge in any order,\n    - Here the letters are not tracked by index rather it is tracked based on it's position in th word:",
      "fontSize": 20.31911393907891,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4. Alogrithms to Resolve this merge conflict are:  [** This is the core of this collaborative user based Problems ** ]\n    \n1. OT  - Operational Transformation\n        -  Transforms Concurrent Operations during Merging.\n        - The transformation fnc ensures that the effect of operation is adjusted to account for the changes by other  operation.  \n\n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n   \n       \n    \n    Problems: \n            1. The Operations must go through a particular server that handles the Transformation.\n            2. Implementation is a bit complex.\n    \n\n!!! Google uses this OT way to solve the Merge Conflict Problem !!!\n\n\n\n2. CRDT - Conflict Free Repicated Data Types:\n    - CRDT is a data structures designed for the distribured system that automatically resolve conflicts caused by concureent updates.\n    - This ensures eventual consitiency without requirimg coordinate by using mathematical properties that allow operations to merge in any order,\n    - Here the letters are not tracked by index rather it is tracked based on it's position in th word:",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
